Text.SourceString: <portrait=annoyed>Is everything okay with your cabin?//<portrait=happy>Oh, good.//<portrait=normal>How do you like the island so far?
Text.LocalizedString: <portrait=annoyed>Is everything okay with your cabin?//<portrait=happy>Oh, good.//<portrait=normal>How do you like the island so far?

Text.SourceString: That’s great to hear!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s great to hear!

Text.SourceString: That’s great! I hope you find what you’re looking for here.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s great! I hope you find what you’re looking for here.

Text.SourceString: Don’t get discouraged! I hope you find what you’re looking for here.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t get discouraged! I hope you find what you’re looking for here.

Text.SourceString: For sure! I hope you find what you’re looking for here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//We’re certainly happy to have you.
Text.LocalizedString: For sure! I hope you find what you’re looking for here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//We’re certainly happy to have you.

Text.SourceString: If you’re on the way to the recycling center, would you take some of my recycling and drop it off, please?
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re on the way to the recycling center, would you take some of my recycling and drop it off, please?

Text.SourceString: No worries if you can’t.//<portrait=concerned>I’m just so swamped today.
Text.LocalizedString: No worries if you can’t.//<portrait=concerned>I’m just so swamped today.

Text.SourceString: I taught <NpcName>Archie</> to bring back things that don’t look like they belong in the forest when he’s playing out there.
Text.LocalizedString: I taught <NpcName>Archie</> to bring back things that don’t look like they belong in the forest when he’s playing out there.

Text.SourceString: I was hoping he’d bring back trash and empty bottles.//<portrait=annoyed>But instead, he brought home a lot of shiny rocks because they “didn’t look like they belonged.”
Text.LocalizedString: I was hoping he’d bring back trash and empty bottles.//<portrait=annoyed>But instead, he brought home a lot of shiny rocks because they “didn’t look like they belonged.”

Text.SourceString: I don’t have enough space to plant big vegetables like pumpkins.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have enough space to plant big vegetables like pumpkins.

Text.SourceString: Maybe, when I have a chance, I’ll think about expanding my garden a little bit.//<portrait=concerned>But now just isn’t a good time.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe, when I have a chance, I’ll think about expanding my garden a little bit.//<portrait=concerned>But now just isn’t a good time.

Text.SourceString: I was just chatting with <NpcName>Jack</> about starting a small vegetable garden.
Text.LocalizedString: I was just chatting with <NpcName>Jack</> about starting a small vegetable garden.

Text.SourceString: We all can chip in, and everyone can take what they need from it.//<portrait=happy>Sort of like a community garden, yes.
Text.LocalizedString: We all can chip in, and everyone can take what they need from it.//<portrait=happy>Sort of like a community garden, yes.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NpcName>Archie</> wouldn’t bring in so much dirt from the forest.//<portrait=normal>He sees things on the ground, and they’re suddenly “treasures.”
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NpcName>Archie</> wouldn’t bring in so much dirt from the forest.//<portrait=normal>He sees things on the ground, and they’re suddenly “treasures.”

Text.SourceString: *sighs* The house is turning into a treasure trove of moldy rocks.
Text.LocalizedString: *sighs* The house is turning into a treasure trove of moldy rocks.

Text.SourceString: Herbs are easy to grow.//As long as you don’t overwater them, they basically grow themselves.
Text.LocalizedString: Herbs are easy to grow.//As long as you don’t overwater them, they basically grow themselves.

Text.SourceString: You probably have more gardening tips than I do.
Text.LocalizedString: You probably have more gardening tips than I do.

Text.SourceString: Jam makes a great gift.//I make sure to pack some for <NpcName>Joko’s</> family when he goes to visit them.
Text.LocalizedString: Jam makes a great gift.//I make sure to pack some for <NpcName>Joko’s</> family when he goes to visit them.

Text.SourceString: You can make any fruit into jam as long as you have some of those jars for preserves at your farm.
Text.LocalizedString: You can make any fruit into jam as long as you have some of those jars for preserves at your farm.

Text.SourceString: Making a cabinet is easier than you think. It just takes a lot of time.
Text.LocalizedString: Making a cabinet is easier than you think. It just takes a lot of time.

Text.SourceString: How are you today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you today, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Tuesday is a workday for us. Judging by your boots, that seems to be the case for you too!
Text.LocalizedString: Tuesday is a workday for us. Judging by your boots, that seems to be the case for you too!

Text.SourceString: I think the hardest thing to craft is probably a wall clock.//<portrait=normal>But for me, a nice wall clock is what completes a house.
Text.LocalizedString: I think the hardest thing to craft is probably a wall clock.//<portrait=normal>But for me, a nice wall clock is what completes a house.

Text.SourceString: Have you watched the weather channel today?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you watched the weather channel today?

Text.SourceString: Hot Summer days are best spent eating freshly harvested melons.//<portrait=happy>My nephew <NpcName>Surya</> and <NpcName>Millie</> both love them too.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot Summer days are best spent eating freshly harvested melons.//<portrait=happy>My nephew <NpcName>Surya</> and <NpcName>Millie</> both love them too.

Text.SourceString: Too bad you can’t grow them year-round, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Too bad you can’t grow them year-round, though.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Dinda</> is singing in another language.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Dinda</> is singing in another language.]

Text.SourceString: Favorite fruit? Hmm…//I have to go with melon.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite fruit? Hmm…//I have to go with melon.

Text.SourceString: You can tell how sweet a melon is by pushing on the spot where the vine was attached.//It should release a sweet scent.
Text.LocalizedString: You can tell how sweet a melon is by pushing on the spot where the vine was attached.//It should release a sweet scent.

Text.SourceString: Typically, it takes me two to three days to complete a project.//<portrait=happy>So it would be wise for you to plan ahead before committing to one.
Text.LocalizedString: Typically, it takes me two to three days to complete a project.//<portrait=happy>So it would be wise for you to plan ahead before committing to one.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I usually spend our Saturday mornings doing yoga at the community center.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I usually spend our Saturday mornings doing yoga at the community center.

Text.SourceString: It’s a great way to socialize.//Catch up with a lot of neighbors in one go.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a great way to socialize.//Catch up with a lot of neighbors in one go.

Text.SourceString: We’re closed today.//It’s not urgent, is it?
Text.LocalizedString: We’re closed today.//It’s not urgent, is it?

Text.SourceString: Clocks are fun to make.//Don’t get me wrong, some of them are hard to craft, but they’re fun regardless.
Text.LocalizedString: Clocks are fun to make.//Don’t get me wrong, some of them are hard to craft, but they’re fun regardless.

Text.SourceString: With all the land you have, farming could be a good way to make some fast money.
Text.LocalizedString: With all the land you have, farming could be a good way to make some fast money.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I rely a lot on furniture sales.//<portrait=normal>Construction projects are a great way to make some cash because we’re paid up front, but let’s face it!//<portrait=concerned>Big projects don’t come around often.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I rely a lot on furniture sales.//<portrait=normal>Construction projects are a great way to make some cash because we’re paid up front, but let’s face it!//<portrait=concerned>Big projects don’t come around often.

Text.SourceString: We live by the forest. Nothing beats the silent evenings.//<portrait=happy>For me, life couldn’t get any better than this.
Text.LocalizedString: We live by the forest. Nothing beats the silent evenings.//<portrait=happy>For me, life couldn’t get any better than this.

Text.SourceString: You need to have enough money to pay for a project before we can start on it.
Text.LocalizedString: You need to have enough money to pay for a project before we can start on it.

Text.SourceString: You also need to provide the building materials.
Text.LocalizedString: You also need to provide the building materials.

Text.SourceString: It’s finally Friday.//We have yoga in front of the community center tomorrow. If it isn’t raining, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s finally Friday.//We have yoga in front of the community center tomorrow. If it isn’t raining, that is.

Text.SourceString: The shop will be closed tomorrow.//We’re heading down to the community center in the morning.
Text.LocalizedString: The shop will be closed tomorrow.//We’re heading down to the community center in the morning.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to relax and work on my flexibility.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to relax and work on my flexibility.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie</> loves playing with <NPCName>Taco</>.//<portrait=concerned>I just hope he isn’t bothering <NpcName>Bree</> too much.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie</> loves playing with <NPCName>Taco</>.//<portrait=concerned>I just hope he isn’t bothering <NpcName>Bree</> too much.

Text.SourceString: I hope you’re doing well today, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you’re doing well today, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: You need to have enough money before we can start a project.//We require payment up front.
Text.LocalizedString: You need to have enough money before we can start a project.//We require payment up front.

Text.SourceString: Are you enjoying your Sunday so far?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you enjoying your Sunday so far?

Text.SourceString: Mine has been good. Thank you for asking.
Text.LocalizedString: Mine has been good. Thank you for asking.

Text.SourceString: I think I’m going to make some pies for dinner tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’m going to make some pies for dinner tonight.

Text.SourceString: I pulled a muscle on Saturday, trying to stretch.
Text.LocalizedString: I pulled a muscle on Saturday, trying to stretch.

Text.SourceString: My leg still feels a bit funny now.//Hopefully, it’ll be better soon.
Text.LocalizedString: My leg still feels a bit funny now.//Hopefully, it’ll be better soon.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any projects for me?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any projects for me?

Text.SourceString: Smaller items, like a doghouse or a shipping crate, can be finished on the same day they’re ordered.
Text.LocalizedString: Smaller items, like a doghouse or a shipping crate, can be finished on the same day they’re ordered.

Text.SourceString: We always have the parts on hand because they’re so popular.//So all I need to do is put them together.
Text.LocalizedString: We always have the parts on hand because they’re so popular.//So all I need to do is put them together.

Text.SourceString: Not all woodwork is complicated.// You can make some simple things yourself.
Text.LocalizedString: Not all woodwork is complicated.// You can make some simple things yourself.

Text.SourceString: I can teach you how to make some of them, but it would be safer to buy the plans.
Text.LocalizedString: I can teach you how to make some of them, but it would be safer to buy the plans.

Text.SourceString: On a slow day like this, I can make two or three shipping crates.
Text.LocalizedString: On a slow day like this, I can make two or three shipping crates.

Text.SourceString: But when I have a big project to work on, I don’t usually do any other crafting. I try not to overwork myself.
Text.LocalizedString: But when I have a big project to work on, I don’t usually do any other crafting. I try not to overwork myself.

Text.SourceString: I guarantee I’ll sleep great tonight after all the stretching I did.
Text.LocalizedString: I guarantee I’ll sleep great tonight after all the stretching I did.

Text.SourceString: It’s bamboo shoot season!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s bamboo shoot season!

Text.SourceString: I’ll have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some Spring vegetables.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some Spring vegetables.

Text.SourceString: I gathered a lot of bamboo shoots over the weekend.//Have you found any yet?
Text.LocalizedString: I gathered a lot of bamboo shoots over the weekend.//Have you found any yet?

Text.SourceString: Try checking around <NpcName>Dippa’s</> house. There may be some over that way.
Text.LocalizedString: Try checking around <NpcName>Dippa’s</> house. There may be some over that way.

Text.SourceString: I’ll have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some shallots.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some shallots.

Text.SourceString: I worry a little when <NpcName>Archie</> gets picky about his food.
Text.LocalizedString: I worry a little when <NpcName>Archie</> gets picky about his food.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, he’ll only want one or two kinds of food for weeks.//<portrait=happy>Good thing he has a healthy appetite for outdoor activity, though, even in this heat.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, he’ll only want one or two kinds of food for weeks.//<portrait=happy>Good thing he has a healthy appetite for outdoor activity, though, even in this heat.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Maybe I’m overthinking this.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Maybe I’m overthinking this.

Text.SourceString: The beach is too far for <NpcName>Archie</> to play there.//I get worried. Especially with all that open water.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is too far for <NpcName>Archie</> to play there.//I get worried. Especially with all that open water.

Text.SourceString: That boy gets into trouble as it is.//I don’t like thinking about what could happen in the water.
Text.LocalizedString: That boy gets into trouble as it is.//I don’t like thinking about what could happen in the water.

Text.SourceString: I’ve hardly noticed that it’s Fall already, what with all the work preparing for the Harvest Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve hardly noticed that it’s Fall already, what with all the work preparing for the Harvest Festival.

Text.SourceString: Exciting time, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Exciting time, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I use leftover logs to make wall clocks in my spare time. I guess you could call it a hobby.
Text.LocalizedString: I use leftover logs to make wall clocks in my spare time. I guess you could call it a hobby.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie</> found a pair of old boots near the cavern yesterday and brought them home.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie</> found a pair of old boots near the cavern yesterday and brought them home.

Text.SourceString: And that’s just one of his “finds.”
Text.LocalizedString: And that’s just one of his “finds.”

Text.SourceString: It’s probably not a good time to start planting pumpkins, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s probably not a good time to start planting pumpkins, huh?

Text.SourceString: Doesn’t it take a while for them to grow?//I’m afraid if you start now, you might not be able to harvest them in time.
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn’t it take a while for them to grow?//I’m afraid if you start now, you might not be able to harvest them in time.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Dinda</> is singing a Winter carol.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Dinda</> is singing a Winter carol.]

Text.SourceString: I worry a little when <NpcName>Archie</> gets picky about his food.
Text.LocalizedString: I worry a little when <NpcName>Archie</> gets picky about his food.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, he’ll only want one or two kinds of food for weeks.//<portrait=happy>Good thing he has a healthy appetite for outdoor activity, though, even in the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, he’ll only want one or two kinds of food for weeks.//<portrait=happy>Good thing he has a healthy appetite for outdoor activity, though, even in the snow.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Maybe I’m overthinking this.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Maybe I’m overthinking this.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you poor thing. It must be so cold out!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you poor thing. It must be so cold out!

Text.SourceString: Have a seat and warm up.
Text.LocalizedString: Have a seat and warm up.

Text.SourceString: Frostbite is a real thing, <PlayerName>$player</>. You be careful, okay?//<portrait=normal>Keep those socks on and keep your feet dry at all times.
Text.LocalizedString: Frostbite is a real thing, <PlayerName>$player</>. You be careful, okay?//<portrait=normal>Keep those socks on and keep your feet dry at all times.

Text.SourceString: Is everything okay? No leaks, I hope?
Text.LocalizedString: Is everything okay? No leaks, I hope?

Text.SourceString: Try not to stand in the rain too long, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I can’t imagine it would be good for your health.
Text.LocalizedString: Try not to stand in the rain too long, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I can’t imagine it would be good for your health.

Text.SourceString: I’m a bit busy. Please feel free to hang out, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a bit busy. Please feel free to hang out, though.

Text.SourceString: Is everything okay? No leaks, I hope?
Text.LocalizedString: Is everything okay? No leaks, I hope?

Text.SourceString: Try not to stand in the rain too long, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I can’t imagine it would be good for your health.
Text.LocalizedString: Try not to stand in the rain too long, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I can’t imagine it would be good for your health.

Text.SourceString: I’m a bit busy. Please feel free to hang out, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a bit busy. Please feel free to hang out, though.

Text.SourceString: My hometown doesn’t get snow, so to me this is unusual.//Even though I’ve lived here almost my whole life, I’m still not used to it yet.
Text.LocalizedString: My hometown doesn’t get snow, so to me this is unusual.//Even though I’ve lived here almost my whole life, I’m still not used to it yet.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait for Spring.//There aren’t many options for fresh flowers this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait for Spring.//There aren’t many options for fresh flowers this time of year.

Text.SourceString: What’s Winter without a little snow, right?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s Winter without a little snow, right?

Text.SourceString: What’s Winter without a little snow, right?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s Winter without a little snow, right?

Text.SourceString: Hot tea sounds good right now. It’s too bad we ran out.//<portrait=concerned>Time to get groceries, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot tea sounds good right now. It’s too bad we ran out.//<portrait=concerned>Time to get groceries, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: Hot tea sounds good right now. It’s too bad we ran out.//<portrait=concerned>Time to get groceries, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot tea sounds good right now. It’s too bad we ran out.//<portrait=concerned>Time to get groceries, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: Good morning!
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning!

Text.SourceString: The best part of the day is seeing the morning mist, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: The best part of the day is seeing the morning mist, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: Keeping these herbs healthy isn’t as easy as it looks.//It took me a couple of months to learn the secret!
Text.LocalizedString: Keeping these herbs healthy isn’t as easy as it looks.//It took me a couple of months to learn the secret!

Text.SourceString: I wonder why my celery keeps wilting.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder why my celery keeps wilting.

Text.SourceString: I can take your order at the counter in a minute.//Do you need anything urgently?
Text.LocalizedString: I can take your order at the counter in a minute.//Do you need anything urgently?

Text.SourceString: Welcome! I don’t have any projects right now, so if you need any building upgrades, we could start first thing tomorrow morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Welcome! I don’t have any projects right now, so if you need any building upgrades, we could start first thing tomorrow morning.

Text.SourceString: Just write down your request at the counter, and <NPCName>Joko</> and I will be there.
Text.LocalizedString: Just write down your request at the counter, and <NPCName>Joko</> and I will be there.

Text.SourceString: Are you looking for anything in particular?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking for anything in particular?

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t give out plastic bags.//There’s no reason we can’t just shove fruit and veggies into our own bags.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t give out plastic bags.//There’s no reason we can’t just shove fruit and veggies into our own bags.

Text.SourceString: There’s already too much plastic in the world.//<portrait=normal>The least we can do is use as little as possible. Reuse your containers, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s already too much plastic in the world.//<portrait=normal>The least we can do is use as little as possible. Reuse your containers, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I could live at the beach like <NpcName>Sunny</> does.//<portrait=normal>The sun is always so intense over there.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I could live at the beach like <NpcName>Sunny</> does.//<portrait=normal>The sun is always so intense over there.

Text.SourceString: It’s great to be in the sun every once in a while, but all the time? I don’t think so.//I need my cool breeze.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s great to be in the sun every once in a while, but all the time? I don’t think so.//I need my cool breeze.

Text.SourceString: I almost cut my finger off chopping wood one time, and all <NpcName>Charles</> did was bandage it up.//<portrait=concerned>He didn’t even give me a tetanus shot.
Text.LocalizedString: I almost cut my finger off chopping wood one time, and all <NpcName>Charles</> did was bandage it up.//<portrait=concerned>He didn’t even give me a tetanus shot.

Text.SourceString: He told me my vaccinations were up to date, and that was it.//I don’t know how to feel about that.
Text.LocalizedString: He told me my vaccinations were up to date, and that was it.//I don’t know how to feel about that.

Text.SourceString: The bad thing about having the workshop connected to the house is all the noise.
Text.LocalizedString: The bad thing about having the workshop connected to the house is all the noise.

Text.SourceString: We do most of our woodworking outdoors, but we still do some of it inside, you know.//So you can imagine how it can disturb the family.
Text.LocalizedString: We do most of our woodworking outdoors, but we still do some of it inside, you know.//So you can imagine how it can disturb the family.

Text.SourceString: We use dovetail joints for all our furniture.//It’s the strongest joint, and the design is aesthetically pleasing.
Text.LocalizedString: We use dovetail joints for all our furniture.//It’s the strongest joint, and the design is aesthetically pleasing.

Text.SourceString: You can still stay inside your cabin tonight, even if you choose to upgrade it.//We don’t usually start work until the morning.
Text.LocalizedString: You can still stay inside your cabin tonight, even if you choose to upgrade it.//We don’t usually start work until the morning.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think <NPCName>Taco</> likes our house very much. Every time he comes in, he goes right back out.//I think it might be too noisy for him.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think <NPCName>Taco</> likes our house very much. Every time he comes in, he goes right back out.//I think it might be too noisy for him.

Text.SourceString: He’s probably used to a bigger place, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s probably used to a bigger place, anyway.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about your boots! No need to take them off.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about your boots! No need to take them off.

Text.SourceString: What brings you here so late, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What brings you here so late, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Have you had dinner? We have some leftovers, if you’d like.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you had dinner? We have some leftovers, if you’d like.

Text.SourceString: There are so many channels. Two would be just fine.//Having this many is overwhelming.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many channels. Two would be just fine.//Having this many is overwhelming.

Text.SourceString: I should just read my book.
Text.LocalizedString: I should just read my book.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice of you to visit, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice of you to visit, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: If you want to see our service, please come back tomorrow.//I should be in the shop and can show it to you then.
Text.LocalizedString: If you want to see our service, please come back tomorrow.//I should be in the shop and can show it to you then.

Text.SourceString: Please help yourself!
Text.LocalizedString: Please help yourself!

Text.SourceString: I found some wasabi earlier. Is it even in season?
Text.LocalizedString: I found some wasabi earlier. Is it even in season?

Text.SourceString: Did you know white oak is the easiest wood to bend?//My father told me that.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know white oak is the easiest wood to bend?//My father told me that.

Text.SourceString: It allows me to make furniture with unusual designs.
Text.LocalizedString: It allows me to make furniture with unusual designs.

Text.SourceString: More people should make it a habit to pick up trash and throw it away.//Even if it wasn’t their trash to begin with.
Text.LocalizedString: More people should make it a habit to pick up trash and throw it away.//Even if it wasn’t their trash to begin with.

Text.SourceString: Imagine what we could achieve if most people did that.
Text.LocalizedString: Imagine what we could achieve if most people did that.

Text.SourceString: What time does yoga start today?
Text.LocalizedString: What time does yoga start today?

Text.SourceString: I did a little warm-up before my yoga session. I feel very awake now.
Text.LocalizedString: I did a little warm-up before my yoga session. I feel very awake now.

Text.SourceString: I’d like to see more classes. It’s a beautiful way to bond with the community.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d like to see more classes. It’s a beautiful way to bond with the community.

Text.SourceString: We never miss a class. You’ll most likely find us here on Saturdays.
Text.LocalizedString: We never miss a class. You’ll most likely find us here on Saturdays.

Text.SourceString: It’s great to see you out and about!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s great to see you out and about!

Text.SourceString: Are you here for the yoga class too, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you here for the yoga class too, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: The mayor? I saw him going toward town earlier.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor? I saw him going toward town earlier.

Text.SourceString: I’m not positive, though. I was a little preoccupied.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not positive, though. I was a little preoccupied.

Text.SourceString: I’m not here to see the mayor.//<portrait=happy>There are plenty of wild vegetables around here. Foraging for them is my one of my favorite things to do.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not here to see the mayor.//<portrait=happy>There are plenty of wild vegetables around here. Foraging for them is my one of my favorite things to do.

Text.SourceString: You should check the lake for mushrooms!//There were plenty over there the other week.
Text.LocalizedString: You should check the lake for mushrooms!//There were plenty over there the other week.

Text.SourceString: Plenty of wild vegetables today!
Text.LocalizedString: Plenty of wild vegetables today!

Text.SourceString: I enjoy gathering wild vegetables.//It’s always exciting to see what nature has to offer.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy gathering wild vegetables.//It’s always exciting to see what nature has to offer.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to come here for a break after work once in a while.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to come here for a break after work once in a while.

Text.SourceString: Plenty of wild vegetables today!
Text.LocalizedString: Plenty of wild vegetables today!

Text.SourceString: These can last us the whole week.
Text.LocalizedString: These can last us the whole week.

Text.SourceString: He’s a great florist. I came here for a bouquet.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s a great florist. I came here for a bouquet.

Text.SourceString: I think it’s admirable that <NpcName>Ben</> tries not to consume animal products.//So keep that in mind when you’re choosing gifts for him.
Text.LocalizedString: I think it’s admirable that <NpcName>Ben</> tries not to consume animal products.//So keep that in mind when you’re choosing gifts for him.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben</> has called me “Doodz” several times. I don’t quite understand.//There’s so much to learn from the young…
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben</> has called me “Doodz” several times. I don’t quite understand.//There’s so much to learn from the young…

Text.SourceString: Oh, he called you that too! What a fun coincidence.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, he called you that too! What a fun coincidence.

Text.SourceString: Oh, we closed early yesterday. I had some errands to run.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, we closed early yesterday. I had some errands to run.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie</> is always getting into something new. Sometimes I wish he’d stick with one thing and get good at it, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie</> is always getting into something new. Sometimes I wish he’d stick with one thing and get good at it, you know?

Text.SourceString: But I guess it’s a process of self-discovery.//At least his interest in rocks seems consistent.
Text.LocalizedString: But I guess it’s a process of self-discovery.//At least his interest in rocks seems consistent.

Text.SourceString: I won’t know what to say when <NpcName>Archie</> starts asking to learn about combat.
Text.LocalizedString: I won’t know what to say when <NpcName>Archie</> starts asking to learn about combat.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell anyone, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I’d hate for <NpcName>Joko</> to hear I’m worrying about that.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell anyone, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I’d hate for <NpcName>Joko</> to hear I’m worrying about that.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> tried to assure me <NpcName>Archie</> will be just fine if he ever decides to be a full-time adventurer.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> tried to assure me <NpcName>Archie</> will be just fine if he ever decides to be a full-time adventurer.

Text.SourceString: I’m just scared he might get hurt.//And I know that boy. Curiosity always gets the best of him.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just scared he might get hurt.//And I know that boy. Curiosity always gets the best of him.

Text.SourceString: We tried to grow melons in our backyard once, but it didn’t work out.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think there’s enough space.
Text.LocalizedString: We tried to grow melons in our backyard once, but it didn’t work out.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think there’s enough space.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. What am I going to do with the rest of my Sunday?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. What am I going to do with the rest of my Sunday?

Text.SourceString: Part of being a parent is worrying too much about what could happen to my son. The hardest part, I’d say.
Text.LocalizedString: Part of being a parent is worrying too much about what could happen to my son. The hardest part, I’d say.

Text.SourceString: Oh no. I’m turning into my father.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no. I’m turning into my father.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie</> will eventually outgrow his shirt. It’s hard to shop for a boy that age.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie</> will eventually outgrow his shirt. It’s hard to shop for a boy that age.

Text.SourceString: I’m afraid he’ll outgrow his new clothes too quickly if I don’t buy a size larger than he needs.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m afraid he’ll outgrow his new clothes too quickly if I don’t buy a size larger than he needs.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think a forest is the best place for children, but <NpcName>Archie</> seems to be doing just fine.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think a forest is the best place for children, but <NpcName>Archie</> seems to be doing just fine.

Text.SourceString: I really should stop worrying about him. It serves no purpose, and it’s just stressing me out.//<portrait=concerned>Easier said than done, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I really should stop worrying about him. It serves no purpose, and it’s just stressing me out.//<portrait=concerned>Easier said than done, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: Nobody was taking care of your grandparents’ farm before.//Yes, everybody helped out and cleared the lot now and then, but it was mostly abandoned.
Text.LocalizedString: Nobody was taking care of your grandparents’ farm before.//Yes, everybody helped out and cleared the lot now and then, but it was mostly abandoned.

Text.SourceString: The massive size of the lot was also a problem. Who knows what kind of animals were living there?//As the parent of a small child, I was always uneasy. Because small children – they wander.//They <Italic>sure</> do, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: The massive size of the lot was also a problem. Who knows what kind of animals were living there?//As the parent of a small child, I was always uneasy. Because small children – they wander.//They <Italic>sure</> do, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad to see the farm in your possession, <PlayerName>$player</>. At least now, if my son wanders over there, I’ll know there’s someone familiar he can ask if he needs help.//<portrait=normal>In case he gets lost or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad to see the farm in your possession, <PlayerName>$player</>. At least now, if my son wanders over there, I’ll know there’s someone familiar he can ask if he needs help.//<portrait=normal>In case he gets lost or something.

Text.SourceString: The craftsmanship of <NpcName>Zarah’s</> boat is incredible.
Text.LocalizedString: The craftsmanship of <NpcName>Zarah’s</> boat is incredible.

Text.SourceString: It would have to be a lot of work, but I bet I could make a boat like that if anybody ever asked me to.
Text.LocalizedString: It would have to be a lot of work, but I bet I could make a boat like that if anybody ever asked me to.

Text.SourceString: My head feels funny, but I feel weirdly energized. It must be that coffee <NPCName>Raj</> was talking about.
Text.LocalizedString: My head feels funny, but I feel weirdly energized. It must be that coffee <NPCName>Raj</> was talking about.

Text.SourceString: We still have some in the kitchen.
Text.LocalizedString: We still have some in the kitchen.

Text.SourceString: I checked out <NpcName>Zarah’s</> boat yesterday while I was in town. The craftsmanship is incredible.
Text.LocalizedString: I checked out <NpcName>Zarah’s</> boat yesterday while I was in town. The craftsmanship is incredible.

Text.SourceString: I can tell it’s made of top-quality wood.
Text.LocalizedString: I can tell it’s made of top-quality wood.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to harvest some herbs for dinner tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to harvest some herbs for dinner tonight.

Text.SourceString: I’ll wait until after work to do it. That way, they’ll be fresh.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll wait until after work to do it. That way, they’ll be fresh.

Text.SourceString: I water my plants every day, but some of the basil wilted anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: I water my plants every day, but some of the basil wilted anyway.

Text.SourceString: Oh no. I’m afraid the roots might be rotten.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no. I’m afraid the roots might be rotten.

Text.SourceString: You’re welcome to take some herbs if you’d like, <PlayerName>$player</>. I grew them myself. All organic!
Text.LocalizedString: You’re welcome to take some herbs if you’d like, <PlayerName>$player</>. I grew them myself. All organic!

Text.SourceString: Take a look at my new wall clock.//I just came up with this design!
Text.LocalizedString: Take a look at my new wall clock.//I just came up with this design!

Text.SourceString: *mumbling to herself* I need to get some eggs tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling to herself* I need to get some eggs tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: We only take orders in the shop.//Go there tomorrow, and I can give you a quote!
Text.LocalizedString: We only take orders in the shop.//Go there tomorrow, and I can give you a quote!

Text.SourceString: I’m hoping to find some mushrooms to grill for dinner tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m hoping to find some mushrooms to grill for dinner tonight.

Text.SourceString: Oh well! There’s always tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well! There’s always tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie’s</> room is always so messy. I don’t even know why I bother cleaning up after him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie’s</> room is always so messy. I don’t even know why I bother cleaning up after him.

Text.SourceString: It takes way too much time, and let’s face it, it’ll be messy again as soon as he comes home anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: It takes way too much time, and let’s face it, it’ll be messy again as soon as he comes home anyway.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie</> – that boy brings everything home.//<portrait=annoyed>Rocks, empty bottles, binoculars, sick animals.<Italic>Everything.</>
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie</> – that boy brings everything home.//<portrait=annoyed>Rocks, empty bottles, binoculars, sick animals.<Italic>Everything.</>

Text.SourceString: His heart’s in the right place, I suppose.
Text.LocalizedString: His heart’s in the right place, I suppose.

Text.SourceString: Some people still go to the hot spring in Summer.//I don’t know how they do it.
Text.LocalizedString: Some people still go to the hot spring in Summer.//I don’t know how they do it.

Text.SourceString: I’m just scared I might pass out if I take a hot bath in this heat.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just scared I might pass out if I take a hot bath in this heat.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Taco</> swimming in town yesterday.//Should I be worried?
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Taco</> swimming in town yesterday.//Should I be worried?

Text.SourceString: I talked to <NpcName>Joko</> about it, but he said <NPCName>Taco</> is a snow dog – something like that.//<portrait=concerned>Is that right? Snow dog? He does look like a small bear.//That’s something, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I talked to <NpcName>Joko</> about it, but he said <NPCName>Taco</> is a snow dog – something like that.//<portrait=concerned>Is that right? Snow dog? He does look like a small bear.//That’s something, right?

Text.SourceString: I washed <NpcName>Archie’s</> rubber boots a couple days ago, and they’re still not dry.//The weather makes it impossible to dry boots. It’s just too cold out.
Text.LocalizedString: I washed <NpcName>Archie’s</> rubber boots a couple days ago, and they’re still not dry.//The weather makes it impossible to dry boots. It’s just too cold out.

Text.SourceString: I guess he’ll have to wear his regular shoes for now.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess he’ll have to wear his regular shoes for now.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad <NpcName>Surya</> lives with us instead of spending his money on rent.//Besides, he eats better here than he would if he ate out all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad <NpcName>Surya</> lives with us instead of spending his money on rent.//Besides, he eats better here than he would if he ate out all the time.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I spent almost all our savings opening the furniture store in town.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I spent almost all our savings opening the furniture store in town.

Text.SourceString: It was a little risky, but it was the only way we could expand our business.//<portrait=normal>People always need new furniture, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: It was a little risky, but it was the only way we could expand our business.//<portrait=normal>People always need new furniture, I guess.

Text.SourceString: We’re grateful to have our cousins working at the store.//We can trust them, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re grateful to have our cousins working at the store.//We can trust them, you know.

Text.SourceString: It would be nice to make a habit of walking to town in the morning. Maybe <NpcName>Joko</> and I could get coffee together or something.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be nice to make a habit of walking to town in the morning. Maybe <NpcName>Joko</> and I could get coffee together or something.

Text.SourceString: With watering my garden and having to open the shop at 9 am, I’m just not sure we’d have enough time.
Text.LocalizedString: With watering my garden and having to open the shop at 9 am, I’m just not sure we’d have enough time.

Text.SourceString: I’m making sure to teach <NpcName>Surya</> how to cook his favorite meals. Well, basic dishes, at least.//<portrait=concerned>I think making lodeh might be a stretch.//<portrait=normal>Anyway, cooking is an important skill for everyone, not just girls.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m making sure to teach <NpcName>Surya</> how to cook his favorite meals. Well, basic dishes, at least.//<portrait=concerned>I think making lodeh might be a stretch.//<portrait=normal>Anyway, cooking is an important skill for everyone, not just girls.

Text.SourceString: Everybody’s gotta eat.
Text.LocalizedString: Everybody’s gotta eat.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I had a meeting at the school the other day, <NpcName>Archie’s</> parent-teacher conference.//It went pretty well.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> and I had a meeting at the school the other day, <NpcName>Archie’s</> parent-teacher conference.//It went pretty well.

Text.SourceString: Except for the part when <NpcName>Randy</> told us <NpcName>Archie</> sometimes goes back to class with muddy shoes after recess.
Text.LocalizedString: Except for the part when <NpcName>Randy</> told us <NpcName>Archie</> sometimes goes back to class with muddy shoes after recess.

Text.SourceString: You’re one of our best customers.//Thank you for supporting us.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re one of our best customers.//Thank you for supporting us.

Text.SourceString: With all the business you’ve given us, you might put <NpcName>Archie</> through school. Ha ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: With all the business you’ve given us, you might put <NpcName>Archie</> through school. Ha ha ha!
